@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Architecture and Governance";
}

<section class="content-page reveal">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p>
        This frontend maps directly to the 3-tier architecture requested in the case study:
        MVC presentation, Web API business services, and EF Core repository-backed data access.
    </p>

    <div class="content-grid">
        <article>
            <h3>Security Baseline</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>JWT access and refresh token workflow</li>
                <li>Role-based UI segments for Admin and Customer</li>
                <li>Versioned endpoints such as /api/v1/books and /api/v1/orders</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Validation Strategy</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Client-side checks via Razor helpers and annotations</li>
                <li>FluentValidation on API layer for business rules</li>
                <li>Consistent error envelopes through global middleware</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Deployment Path</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>MVC and API on Azure App Service</li>
                <li>Azure SQL Database and Blob Storage integration</li>
                <li>GitHub Actions or Azure DevOps CI/CD pipeline</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
